FBIS3-31348 "dreeu033_y_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-033 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Feb 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Serbia Extends Stay in Belgrade LD1602172894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1647 GMT 16 Feb 94 LD1602172894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Belgrade, 16 Feb (TANJUG) -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin, who arrived today on a suprise visit to Belgrade where he met Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, will extend his stay in the Yugoslav capital by another day, TANJUG has learned from the office of the Russian NOVOSTI news agency in Belgrade. The same source disclosed that Churkin's latest visit to Belgrade is directly linked to the situation in Sarajevo -- the NATO ultimatum -- and threats that Serb positions around that city will be attacked if the artillery is not withdrawn to a distance of 20 km from Sarajevo. [passage omitted]
